name: Spencer Cox
tweet: So grateful for our rural first responders who worked through terrible conditions to rescue the injured last night.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: I never had a chance to interact with Tom, but his voice is unmistakeable. I would say he is one of a kind…but I know Gina. So I suppose they are two of a kind. Utah is better because of the Barberi family and I’m grateful his legacy lives on. Rest In Peace Tom.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: @taryn_aiken Merry Christmas and congratulations! We are so happy for you.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: Blessed Christmas. Today we pray that peace, forgiveness, understanding and joy will fill your hearts. May every burden be a little lighter as we lift together.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: In the past I always hoped for snow on Christmas night, but that changed when I started spending time with our snow plow drivers and @UTHighwayPatrol troopers. Thank you for sacrificing time with your families so we can be with ours. Please be safe tonight and always.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: @WasatchSnow I would feel bad…except we got missed with the last two storms. Snow water equivalent in the Sanpitch Drainage jumped from 55% to 76% overnight…and it’s still nuking out there.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: 10 inches of heavy and wet snow (plus lots of rain before that)…and still dumping in Fairview. Power has been out since 6:30. Happy Christmas Eve!  https://t.co/D1s4hg7pZ2

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: @For3JT We’ve seen a few bears and cougars in this area. No wolves. Bears usually hibernating this time of year. Nothing to be concerned about. They like to stay away from people.

name: Spencer Cox
tweet: This makes me sad. Michael was a great reporter and a better person. He loved to talk to me about his ties to Sanpete and even came to my son’s missionary farewell. He was committed to his craft and the people of Utah. We will miss him dearly.
